# This is a comment to explain the purpose of this .gitignore file.
# It is used by Git to determine which files and directories to ignore
# when committing code. This helps keep the repository clean from
# unnecessary or sensitive files.


# Ignore IDE-specific settings files.
# This ensures that personal editor configurations are not shared
# across the team.
.vscode/

# Ignore Markdown files that are for documentation or project management,
# not part of the core application code.
ADVANCED_FEATURES.md
README.md
.DS_Store
